.TH "_drbd_request_state" 9 "_drbd_request_state" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_drbd_request_state \- Request a state change (with flags)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "enum drbd_state_rv" _drbd_request_state
.BI "(struct drbd_device *device "  ","
.BI "union drbd_state mask "  ","
.BI "union drbd_state val "  ","
.BI "enum chg_state_flags f "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
DRBD device.
.IP "mask" 12
mask of state bits to change.
.IP "val" 12
value of new state bits.
.IP "f" 12
flags
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Cousin of \fBdrbd_request_state\fP, useful with the CS_WAIT_COMPLETE
flag, or when logging of failed state change requests is not desired.
